## Styling Guidelines

### Color System

**IMPORTANT:** Always use semantic color tokens, never hardcoded colors.

**Available color tokens:**
```typescript
// Surface colors (backgrounds)
bg-surface-light                    // Light mode widget background
bg-surface-light-elevated           // Light mode elevated elements (cards)
bg-surface-dark                     // Dark mode widget background (#000000)
bg-surface-dark-elevated            // Dark mode elevated elements (#121212)

// Text colors
text-text-light-primary             // Primary text (light mode)
text-text-light-secondary           // Secondary text (light mode)
text-text-dark-primary              // Primary text (dark mode)
text-text-dark-secondary            // Secondary text (dark mode)

// Accent colors (buttons, links, highlights)
bg-accent-blue                      // Primary action blue
bg-accent-blue-hover                // Blue hover state
bg-accent-magenta                   // Secondary accent magenta
bg-accent-cyan                      // Tertiary accent cyan
text-accent-blue                    // Blue text

// Status colors
text-status-error                   // Error red
text-status-success                 // Success green
text-status-warning                 // Warning orange

// Border colors
border-border-light                 // Light mode borders
border-border-dark                  // Dark mode borders
```

**Example:**
```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Uses semantic tokens
<div className="bg-surface-light-elevated dark:bg-surface-dark rounded p-3">
  <h3 className="text-text-light-primary dark:text-text-dark-primary font-semibold">
    Title
  </h3>
  <p className="text-text-light-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary text-sm">
    Description
  </p>
</div>

// ❌ WRONG - Hardcoded colors
<div className="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800">
  <h3 className="text-black dark:text-white">Title</h3>
</div>
```

### Responsive Design

Widgets must adapt to different container sizes (resizable in Dashboard):

```typescript
// ✅ Use responsive utilities
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-2">
  {/* Grid adapts to widget width */}
</div>

// ✅ Use flexbox for flexibility
<div className="flex flex-col gap-2 h-full">
  {/* Content stretches to fill height */}
</div>

// ✅ Use w-full and h-full
<div className="w-full h-full overflow-auto">
  {/* Widget fills available space */}
</div>
```

### Accessibility

All widgets must meet WCAG AA standards:

```typescript
// ✅ Use semantic HTML
<button onClick={handleClick}>Click me</button> // Not <div onClick>

// ✅ Add ARIA labels
<button aria-label="Refresh weather data" onClick={refresh}>
  🔄
</button>

// ✅ Keyboard navigation
<input
  onKeyDown={(e) => e.key === 'Enter' && handleSubmit()}
  aria-label="Search query"
/>

// ✅ Focus states
<button className="focus:ring-2 focus:ring-accent-blue">
  Submit
</button>
```

